            <thetext>In Firefox 3.6 we used to ignore updates offered for hardblocked items. The code comments suggest that we warned about soft blocked items but I&apos;m not sure that is true. In 4.0 we lost this and now just update to the newest version regardless of whether it is blocked.

Since we are now doing automatic silent updates for add-ons I don&apos;t think we should update even if it is only soft blocked. We wouldn&apos;t want to show UI to warn the user and we wouldn&apos;t want to disable the add-on automatically either I think.</thetext>
